1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:14.630
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:17.540
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:20.370
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:23.480
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.110
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:41.040
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:46.560
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:52.100
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:56.080
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:02.700
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.990
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:05.990 --> 00:01:09.220
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:21.120
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:24.200
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:30.220
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.460 --> 00:01:33.580
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.750
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.350
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:50.010 --> 00:01:53.680
<b>Showdown at Alubarna</b>

21
00:01:57.390 --> 00:02:01.360
That's when it happened!
That's when I said to him,

22
00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:03.900
"You bowlegged bastard!"

23
00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:05.350
Ever since that day,

24
00:02:05.350 --> 00:02:08.520
the world's crabs have been
insecure about being bowlegged.

25
00:02:10.190 --> 00:02:11.990
So that's why they walk sideways?

26
00:02:11.990 --> 00:02:16.030
Uh-huh. But some of them
would hop backwards instead.

27
00:02:16.030 --> 00:02:17.530
I called them "prawns".

28
00:02:18.660 --> 00:02:20.950
So prawns are just crabs?

29
00:02:20.950 --> 00:02:22.860
Yeah, they're crabs.

30
00:02:24.670 --> 00:02:28.510
Zoro, aren't you just wasting
your energy doing that?

31
00:02:28.510 --> 00:02:29.720
Shut up.

32
00:02:29.720 --> 00:02:32.470
Just leave them be, Nami.

33
00:02:32.470 --> 00:02:36.760
Those guys need to keep busy
so they don't dwell on things.

34
00:02:36.760 --> 00:02:39.470
They're primitive like that. Especially...

35
00:02:42.180 --> 00:02:46.270
that meathead, now that he's
had a taste of the Warlords' strength.

36
00:02:47.310 --> 00:02:49.860
Hey, you, what are you trying to say?

37
00:02:50.350 --> 00:02:51.620
Go ahead and spell it out.

38
00:02:51.620 --> 00:02:53.820
Ah, you want me to say it?

39
00:02:53.820 --> 00:02:58.780
You're scared. You're worried
that Luffy might lose.

40
00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:04.120
Who, me?! You calling me scared?!
You're nothing but...

41
00:03:04.120 --> 00:03:05.210
fancy eyebrows!

42
00:03:05.210 --> 00:03:08.000
That's it! Now you've done it...

43
00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:09.900
Moss Head!

44
00:03:09.900 --> 00:03:10.880
What?!

45
00:03:11.490 --> 00:03:13.350
You wanna go at it?!

46
00:03:15.150 --> 00:03:17.340
Cut it out! This is pointless.

47
00:03:19.090 --> 00:03:23.050
They can't help themselves.
Everyone's a bit wound up.

48
00:03:23.050 --> 00:03:25.280
Now's the time for me,
the vice captain, to–

49
00:03:25.280 --> 00:03:27.660
Calm down, everyone.

50
00:03:27.130 --> 00:03:27.660
Huh?

51
00:03:27.660 --> 00:03:30.730
Luffy won't lose. I mean,
we promised him, didn't we?

52
00:03:30.730 --> 00:03:33.440
That we'd be waiting
for him in Alubarna?

53
00:03:33.440 --> 00:03:36.030
You seem more worried
than anyone here!

54
00:03:37.370 --> 00:03:38.180
Ow!

55
00:03:38.180 --> 00:03:40.990
You just worry about the rebellion.

56
00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:43.700
Sorry about that, Vivi.

57
00:03:43.700 --> 00:03:46.660
If you have to reassure us,
we're done for.

58
00:03:47.760 --> 00:03:50.740
All right, then switch
your minds over to Alubarna!

59
00:03:50.740 --> 00:03:53.400
Let's go, Pincers!

60
00:03:56.270 --> 00:03:57.250
What's that?

61
00:03:57.250 --> 00:03:58.560
A name for the crab.

62
00:03:59.620 --> 00:04:00.770
"Pincers," you say?

63
00:04:00.770 --> 00:04:02.470
– Got a problem with it?
– Nope. No problem.

64
00:04:05.480 --> 00:04:10.270
<b>Yuba
Former Rebel Base Camp</b>

65
00:04:12.690 --> 00:04:15.940
Look! Th-There's so much!

66
00:04:17.440 --> 00:04:19.390
The water...

67
00:04:21.030 --> 00:04:23.320
The water is coming forth!

68
00:04:25.370 --> 00:04:27.650
Didn't I tell you, Luffy?

69
00:04:28.830 --> 00:04:30.750
This land is strong.

70
00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:36.170
Yuba still lives.

71
00:04:40.240 --> 00:04:42.130
Yuba will die...

72
00:04:42.130 --> 00:04:45.600
from that one, final sandstorm.

73
00:04:46.360 --> 00:04:50.720
And then, the flame of anger in
the Rebel Army will burn even hotter.

74
00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:58.530
This outmoded compassion for others
will be this land's downfall.

75
00:04:59.990 --> 00:05:03.950
And the same goes for you,
Straw Hat Luffy.

76
00:05:04.610 --> 00:05:08.870
If you had abandoned this useless
compassion, you'd have lived longer.

77
00:05:11.780 --> 00:05:13.710
Water...?

78
00:05:13.710 --> 00:05:17.920
I doubt you still feel
indebted to this water, huh?

79
00:05:30.890 --> 00:05:34.060
What's that? You're still alive?

80
00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:57.420
That looks painful. But you'll
be out of your misery soon enough.

81
00:06:06.180 --> 00:06:08.250
Bye, now.

82
00:06:13.030 --> 00:06:15.870
What a waste of my time.

83
00:06:28.420 --> 00:06:34.740
No big deal. Once the dust
subsides, it will rain.

84
00:06:34.740 --> 00:06:36.580
Just like always.

85
00:06:38.750 --> 00:06:42.720
Bring it on! Bring it on, sandstorms—
as often as you dare!

86
00:06:43.220 --> 00:06:47.890
Yuba will never give in to the sand!

87
00:06:56.050 --> 00:06:57.990
Me, go to Alubarna?

88
00:06:59.230 --> 00:07:01.400
To go after the Straw Hat
Pirates, right?

89
00:07:01.400 --> 00:07:04.210
Or should we assist the Royal Army?

90
00:07:04.210 --> 00:07:05.820
It's up to you.

91
00:07:07.060 --> 00:07:10.370
You decide what to do
when you're there.

92
00:07:10.840 --> 00:07:13.620
But that... What do you
mean by that?

93
00:07:14.070 --> 00:07:16.580
You just follow your sense of justice.

94
00:07:17.380 --> 00:07:21.130
Whatever happens,
I'll accept responsibility.

95
00:07:22.850 --> 00:07:24.720
Captain Smoker,
where are you going?

96
00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:27.430
Something urgent came up.
I'm heading back to sea.

97
00:07:28.180 --> 00:07:30.680
Stay prepared for my call, Tashigi.

98
00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:31.890
Of course.

99
00:07:33.350 --> 00:07:36.350
Keep a close eye on what
becomes of this country.

100
00:07:39.720 --> 00:07:41.860
Whether it endures or crumbles,

101
00:07:41.860 --> 00:07:45.530
these events will herald
the dawn of a new era.

102
00:07:52.490 --> 00:07:55.540
Chief... Chief Petty Officer!

103
00:07:55.540 --> 00:07:57.160
Your orders?

104
00:07:57.160 --> 00:07:57.750
Right...

105
00:08:00.270 --> 00:08:03.940
Keep a close watch on
where this country ends up.

106
00:08:03.940 --> 00:08:06.100
Whether it endures or crumbles,

107
00:08:06.100 --> 00:08:09.760
these events will herald
the dawn of a new era.

108
00:08:13.370 --> 00:08:17.470
We're going after the pirate
Straw Hat Luffy and his crew!

109
00:08:17.470 --> 00:08:21.730
All hands, take up arms!
Prepare to depart for Alubarna!

110
00:08:21.730 --> 00:08:22.440
– Yes, ma'am!
– Yes, ma'am!

111
00:08:24.450 --> 00:08:26.150
Straw Hat Luffy...

112
00:08:35.410 --> 00:08:40.640
Just you wait, Cobra.
We're going to defend Alabasta.

113
00:08:40.640 --> 00:08:43.010
We won't surrender its fate to you!

114
00:08:47.420 --> 00:08:52.340
<b>Alubarna, the Capital</b>

115
00:08:52.340 --> 00:08:55.480
Ready cannons at the south gate!
Stop dawdling! Hurry!

116
00:08:55.480 --> 00:08:57.850
Bring more cannonballs over here!

117
00:09:01.650 --> 00:09:02.770
Commander Chaka!

118
00:09:03.910 --> 00:09:07.030
The enemy's numbers are said
to be well over two million!

119
00:09:08.240 --> 00:09:12.650
What do you think of His Majesty's
attack on Nanohana?

120
00:09:12.650 --> 00:09:16.520
I have served him for
ten years, so I was quite...

121
00:09:16.520 --> 00:09:19.460
Yeah. There's really no way
anyone could believe it.

122
00:09:20.240 --> 00:09:23.420
I can only presume that
something happened to the king.

123
00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:29.760
And if so, it's all the more reason
why we must not lose this fight.

124
00:09:29.760 --> 00:09:31.680
Do not flinch at the enemy's number.

125
00:09:31.680 --> 00:09:35.600
For the good of the king
and the return of Princess Vivi,

126
00:09:36.100 --> 00:09:38.560
we will defend this country!

127
00:09:39.480 --> 00:09:42.850
Everyone not joining the battle,
take shelter outside the city!

128
00:09:42.850 --> 00:09:45.400
We cannot guarantee
your safety if you stay!

129
00:09:45.400 --> 00:09:49.400
Run! We're going to be
caught in the crossfire!

130
00:09:51.310 --> 00:09:54.370
Things are finally starting
to become hectic, huh?

131
00:09:54.850 --> 00:09:56.660
Speed up this riot, already, ok?

132
00:09:56.660 --> 00:09:58.580
Things are so slow, I can't stand it.

133
00:10:04.490 --> 00:10:07.420
He's a king! He's a king! I don't care!

134
00:10:07.420 --> 00:10:10.580
I can't watch him
much longer, I swear!

135
00:10:10.580 --> 00:10:13.630
Can't take it! Can't, can't,
for crying out loud!

136
00:10:15.760 --> 00:10:18.390
I mean, sure, slipping past
the palace guards

137
00:10:18.390 --> 00:10:22.860
and kidnapping this guy was a mission
that only we could carry out,

138
00:10:22.860 --> 00:10:25.740
but now that's done,
and it's like we're watching paint dry!

139
00:10:25.740 --> 00:10:27.400
Right, Mr. 4?

140
00:10:28.100 --> 00:10:29.270
Did you hear me?

141
00:10:29.270 --> 00:10:32.020
You are so slow
at answering me, seriously!

142
00:10:33.360 --> 00:10:34.950
Ah, my back hurts!
My back! My ba...

143
00:10:34.950 --> 00:10:37.320
Chaka... Koza...

144
00:10:37.760 --> 00:10:42.260
You must stop this conflict. You are
the ones that define this country.

145
00:10:42.260 --> 00:10:44.280
This fight can only bring destruction.

146
00:10:46.800 --> 00:10:48.960
Those who lament war...

147
00:10:55.290 --> 00:10:57.300
Those who go to war...

148
00:11:04.480 --> 00:11:06.300
Go on, run away!

149
00:11:08.420 --> 00:11:10.740
Those who incite war...

150
00:11:13.740 --> 00:11:17.000
Those who, knowing the truth,
want to prevent it...

151
